  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Boil half a kettle</p><p>Cut your <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into wedges, then add them to a large baking tray (or two!) with a drizzle of<strong> vegetable oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for 20-25 min or until the wedges are golden and starting to crisp</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1619.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1619.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1619.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1619.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1619.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the wedges are cooking, slice your <strong>cucumber</strong> in half lengthways, then slice the halves into wedges</p><p>Add your <strong>red wine vinegar</strong>, <strong>yellow</strong> <strong>mustard seeds</strong>, 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong>, a splash of <strong>boiled water </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> to a bowl and stir until dissolved</p><p>Add the<strong> cucumber wedges </strong>to the bowl and give everything a good mix up, then set aside – these are your <strong>quick-pickled cucumber wedges</strong></p><p>Tip: Give the cucumber the occasional shake while pickling!</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1619.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1619.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1619.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1619.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1619.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) over a medium heat</p><p>Slice your <strong>brioche bun[s] </strong>in half</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>brioche halves</strong>, cut-side down, and cook for 2-3 min or until toasted, then set them aside until serving, reserve the pan</p><p>Tip: Cooking for 3 or more? You may need to do this in batches!</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1619.-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1619.-step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1619.-step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1619.-step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1619.-step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your<strong> beef mince</strong> and <strong>soy sauce</strong> to a large bowl with a generous grind of <strong>black</strong> <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Knead thoroughly until fully combined (kneading the patty[ies] for longer will make it more tender!)</p><p>Shape into 1<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span><strong>burger patty </strong>per person</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1619.-step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1619.-step-4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1619.-step-4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1619.-step-4-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1619.-step-4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the pan to a high heat with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>burger patty[ies]</strong>, press down firmly with a spatula and cook for 5 min</p><p>Tip: Cooking for 5? You may need to do this in batches!</p><p>Flip the <strong>patty[ies]</strong> and reduce the heat to medium-high and cook for 5 min further until cooked through and charred (no pink meat!)</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1619.-step-5-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1619.-step-5-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1619.-step-5-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1619.-step-5-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1619.-step-5-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, combine your <strong>mayo</strong>, <strong>tomato ketchup</strong> and <strong>mustard ketchup </strong>in a small bowl – this is your <strong>special sauce</strong></p><p>Grate your <strong>cheddar cheese</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1619.-step-6-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1619.-step-6-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1619.-step-6-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1619.-step-6-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1619.-step-6-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once cooked, add the <strong>grated cheese</strong> on top of each <strong>burger patty</strong> and cook, covered, for 1-2 min further or until the cheese has melted – this is your <strong>cheeseburger patty</strong></p><p>Drain the <strong>quick-pickled</strong> <strong>cucumber wedges </strong>and discard the liquid</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1619.-step-7-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1619.-step-7-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1619.-step-7-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1619.-step-7-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1619.-step-7-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>To assemble, spread the <strong>special sauce </strong>onto the <strong>toasted brioche base</strong>, then top with a <strong>cheeseburger patty</strong>, a sprinkling of <strong>crispy onions </strong>and a <strong>toasted brioche lid</strong> – this is your <strong>American-style</strong> <strong>cheeseburger</strong></p><p>Serve the <strong>potato wedges </strong>and<strong> quick-pickled cucumber wedges</strong> to the side</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
